data.name: checkBoxWarmupPass.ToolTip
data.value:
Enables a short warm-up pass before benchmarking begins.
When enabled: All encoders start under identical thermal and CPU frequency conditions, ensuring fair comparison.
When disabled: The first test pass may show slower performance due to CPU frequency ramp-up (turbo boost not yet active).

data.name: buttonTestForErrors.ToolTip
data.value:
Tests all FLAC files in the list (both checked and unchecked) for integrity errors. If errors are found, they are displayed in the "Test for Errors" tab of the Log. Needs a FLAC binary loaded in the list. Uses first checked binary or first one if nothing is checked.
Consider enabling the "Warnings as Errors" option to see additional diagnostic messages.
Warnings: • There is no progress indicator - checking many files may take a long time. • The operation can be resource-intensive when processing a large number of files.

data.name: buttonDetectDupesAudioFiles.ToolTip
data.value:
Identifies duplicate audio files by comparing MD5 hashes of their raw PCM data. Scans all files in the list (both checked and unchecked).
When duplicates are found: • Duplicate groups are moved to the top of the list; • The primary file in each group remains checked (FLAC > WAV, newer > older, shorter path > longer); • All other duplicates are automatically unchecked; • You can then use "Clear unchecked" to remove them from list (or 'Shift' + click to move them to the Recycle Bin).
Results are displayed in the "Detect Dupes" tab of the Log.
Note: In some cases, this process may also reveal corrupted files (e.g., if MD5 calculation fails).
Warnings: • There is no progress indicator - processing many files may take a long time. • The operation can be resource-intensive when handling a large number of files.

data.name: buttonAnalyzeLog.ToolTip
data.value:
Analyzes and consolidates encoding results by file, encoder, and parameters.
Identifies the fastest en/de-coder and smallest output size for each file, and detects duplicate sizes across configurations.
Perform this before exporting the log to Excel.

data.name: checkBoxRemoveMetadata.ToolTip
data.value:
Run "metaflac.exe --remove-all --dont-use-padding" after encoding. This reduces the output file size by removing all metadata (tags, covers, etc.).
• Input files are not affected. • The "--no-padding" encoding option is ignored. • Does not affect encoding or decoding speed.
This option is necessary for more accurate file size comparisons when testing different encoders or parameters.
⚠️ WARNING! When enabled, the output file size will differ from standard encoding with applied effects. Use this option only if different encoders show different file sizes for the same input, to eliminate custom metadata or padding that may skew compression results.
